1
00:00:09,933 --> 00:00:11,433
We will get rich!

2
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:15,733
If we will pool
our resources together,

3
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,800
we will get rich together.

4
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:20,400
We will get rich!

5
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:22,900
Son.

6
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:25,400
- What do you want?
- I regret what I did.

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,900
You have no idea what we went
through when you left us.

8
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:30,567
We're already used to you
not being around.

9
00:00:30,667 --> 00:00:33,100
So, please don't bother us.

10
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:35,767
He invited a confrontation.
It's not like your father.

11
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:37,100
So what are you saying?

12
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:39,567
Whatever his reason was
for coming to you,

13
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:41,100
I'm sure it was important.

14
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,267
Is there a problem?
Is he sick?

15
00:00:45,367 --> 00:00:47,333
- [GUNSHOT]
- [PHONE RINGS]

16
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:56,267
Pa? Pa! Pa!

17
00:00:56,367 --> 00:00:58,433
The neighbor said
the gunshot came from here.

18
00:00:58,533 --> 00:01:00,267
Help! Help. Help.

19
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,767
Hey! Get on the ground!
Do as I say!

20
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,833
My father is inside!
I didn't do anything!

21
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:08,067
Possible homicide.
11 Arellano Street.

22
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,700
"Son, why aren't you
home yet?"

23
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:30,133
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

24
00:01:48,867 --> 00:01:52,500
[PHONE RINGS]

25
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:54,667
Hello?

26
00:01:54,767 --> 00:01:56,200
[MAN] Mrs. Lolita Trinidad?

27
00:01:56,367 --> 00:01:58,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

28
00:01:58,667 --> 00:01:59,800
Yes, speaking.

29
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:01,667
Are you Mike Trinidad's wife?

30
00:02:03,867 --> 00:02:04,800
Yes.

31
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,967
Why?

32
00:02:10,067 --> 00:02:12,333
This is Detective
Victor Jacinto

33
00:02:12,433 --> 00:02:15,833
of the Police Investigation
Unit in Station 9.

34
00:02:16,033 --> 00:02:18,700
I have bad news
about your husband.

35
00:02:18,867 --> 00:02:24,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

36
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:27,667
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

37
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,767
[CLICKS]

38
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:39,100
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

39
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:46,767
It's not here.

40
00:02:47,733 --> 00:02:50,467
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- [TAPPING DESK]

41
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:56,933
[SUCKS TEETH]

42
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:58,867
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

43
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:06,933
Why isn't it showing up?

44
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:10,200
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

45
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,067
- [SLAMS DESK]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

46
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:18,367
[GROANS]

47
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:22,100
Why isn't it here?
Why is it empty?!

48
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:24,900
Gah!

49
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:27,167
[HUFFS]

50
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:32,167
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

51
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:35,967
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

52
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:43,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

53
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:48,633
[CLICKING]

54
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,767
Aah!

55
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:51,933
[HUFFS]

56
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:53,933
Why is it empty?!

57
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,167
- Let go of me!
- Stop!

58
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:56,333
This is wrong!

59
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,100
- Liar! Come with us!
- I already told you,

60
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,333
- I didn't do anything!
- Stop explaining!

61
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,467
- [THWACK]
- [GRUNTS]

62
00:04:01,567 --> 00:04:03,033
- Sir!
- Don't touch me!

63
00:04:03,167 --> 00:04:04,133
You're pushing me, huh!

64
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:05,500
- Sir!
- Policarpio, hey!

65
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:07,633
I'm really losing
my patience with you!

66
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,633
- You got the wrong person!
- Wrong person?!

67
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:12,367
- Yes, wrong!
- Hey, get him inside!

68
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:15,633
- Sir!
- Let go of me!

69
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,800
I said let go of me!

70
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,667
- Let's talk outside.
- Why? I'm already bleeding!

71
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:21,333
- I didn't do anything!
- Shut up!

72
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,133
I told you, I'm innocent!

73
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,867
Sit down! Now!

74
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,033
Wait right there!

75
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,867
I didn't kill my father.

76
00:04:30,767 --> 00:04:31,667
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

77
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:33,200
I didn't kill him.

78
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:36,067
I didn't kill my father!

79
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:41,000
The press is all over us

81
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,367
because of cops like you!

82
00:04:42,533 --> 00:04:44,133
What if a reporter saw
what you just did?!

83
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,233
Sir, I'm the one
he headbutted!

84
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:48,333
I don't care why you did it!

85
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:50,333
What I want to hear
from you, Policarpio,

86
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:52,533
is that this will never
happen again!

87
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:54,333
Are we clear?!

88
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:57,200
Look at me!

89
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,467
Do you understand?

90
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:04,367
Yes, sir.

91
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:13,567
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,533
[THUDS]

93
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:30,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

94
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:53,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

95
00:05:55,833 --> 00:06:02,700
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:05,367
Mike Trinidad is dead.

97
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,700
[GLASS SHATTERS]

98
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:11,767
I want to know
where our money is!

99
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:16,400
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,600
Look at this.

101
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,600
That's our suspect.

102
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,767
Samuel Trinidad.

103
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:22,800
Mike's son.

104
00:06:22,967 --> 00:06:24,767
He was the last
person seen with Mike.

105
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,300
The money's with him.

106
00:06:26,467 --> 00:06:33,467
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:39,000
[DOOR CLOSES]

108
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,567
Samuel Trinidad?

109
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,500
I'm Detective
Adrian Palomares.

110
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:47,967
You're the victim's son?

111
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:50,533
Mike Trinidad?

112
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:59,967
Your father left you more
than 20 years ago, correct?

113
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:02,433
How'd you know that?

114
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:04,633
I'm an investigator.
I know a lot.

115
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,100
Are you angry with him?

116
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,500
Are you trying to give me a
motive to kill my own father?

117
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:14,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:18,833
You're a branch manager
at Golden Trust Bank.

119
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,867
On the side,

120
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:24,400
you're into Kali,
Filipino martial arts.

121
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,167
[GRUNTING]

122
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:36,533
[ADRIAN] Impressive. [LAUGHS]

123
00:07:38,233 --> 00:07:40,867
And aside from that,
you're a good...

124
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,500
...shooter too.

125
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:47,300
In fact, you even won
a shooting competition

126
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,300
two years ago. [CHUCKLES]

127
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:51,600
Which means you're trained

128
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:55,933
in hand-to-hand combat
and firearms.

129
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:59,900
In other words,
if you wanted to,

130
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:01,733
you could kill someone.

131
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:04,833
Whatever training I got,

132
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:07,833
you also got
when you became a cop.

133
00:08:09,033 --> 00:08:12,233
So does that mean
you're a killer too, sir?

134
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:18,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

135
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:20,033
That's you, right?

136
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:24,933
Do you visit
your father's house often?

137
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:27,233
No.

138
00:08:27,367 --> 00:08:29,733
- How often do you see him?
- This is my first time.

139
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:32,200
First time you went
to your father's house?

140
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:34,233
What a big coincidence!

141
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:35,800
And the moment you show up,

142
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:39,367
your father, who abandoned you,
is found dead?!

143
00:08:39,467 --> 00:08:40,767
And your clothes
are covered in blood?

144
00:08:40,933 --> 00:08:42,233
You were even
about to run, right?

145
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,767
- I wasn't trying to run!
- But the police caught you!

146
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:46,867
I was trying to get help,
not escape!

147
00:08:46,967 --> 00:08:48,700
You have the ability,
and you have a motive!

148
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:51,400
Just because I was angry
doesn't mean I killed him!

149
00:08:51,567 --> 00:08:53,633
- Just admit it!
- I've got nothing to admit!

150
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:55,533
Nothing!

151
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:57,300
If you really think
my father was killed,

152
00:08:57,467 --> 00:09:00,233
then find out
who really did it,

153
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:02,167
because it wasn't me!

154
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:03,733
Am I interrupting something?

155
00:09:05,667 --> 00:09:06,600
Who are you?

156
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:08,000
Atty. Rafael Antonio.

157
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:09,933
I'm his lawyer.

158
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:11,933
May I speak with
my client, please?

159
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:18,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

160
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,667
[SIGHS]

161
00:09:26,467 --> 00:09:30,100
[TRAFFIC NOISE]

162
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,100
- Come on! Come on!
- Whoo!

163
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,967
- Chug! Chug! Chug!
- Chug! Chug! Chug!

164
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:38,100
[PARTYGOERS CHEERING]

165
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:44,367
- Chug! Chug! Chug!
- Chug! Chug! Chug!

166
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,500
[CHEERING]

167
00:09:47,667 --> 00:09:50,967
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

168
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:55,300
- [MAN] Hey! [COUGHS]
- Three points! Loser!

169
00:09:55,400 --> 00:10:01,267
- [CHEERING]
- [OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

170
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:04,700
[HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]

171
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:11,900
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:23,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:37,867
[RAFAEL] Man,
as your lawyer...

174
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,233
be straight with me.

175
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:41,067
Did you do it?

176
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:45,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

177
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,533
- Even you, man? Seriously?
- Okay, sorry.

178
00:10:48,267 --> 00:10:49,700
I just need to know.

179
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:52,033
I know how much anger
you had toward your father.

180
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,900
I need to know everything.

181
00:10:54,033 --> 00:10:56,033
In case they press charges,

182
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,900
I'll know how to defend you.

183
00:10:58,033 --> 00:11:00,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

184
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,567
You really didn't do it?

185
00:11:02,533 --> 00:11:04,433
- Man, I didn't do it!
- Okay.

186
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:09,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:11:09,233 --> 00:11:10,300
Roldan.

188
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:12,367
Trinidad's been arrested.

189
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:14,100
He's being interrogated
right now.

190
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:16,900
He can't end up in jail.

191
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:19,467
He needs to tell us
where the money is!

192
00:11:21,567 --> 00:11:22,300
Okay.

193
00:11:22,433 --> 00:11:29,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,700
[DOOR CLOSES]

195
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:35,733
[FOLDER THUDS]

196
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,133
[PALOMARES SIGHS]

197
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:39,200
[DOOR SLAMS]

198
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,200
Rigor mortis
had already set in

199
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,067
when the forensic team
examined the body.

200
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:46,433
This puts time of death
between 9PM and 10PM.

201
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:49,500
And based on the
CCTV timestamp,

202
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:53,267
Samuel Trinidad arrived
at around 11:30PM.

203
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,333
He's free to go.

204
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:57,800
Was my father murdered?

205
00:11:59,933 --> 00:12:01,767
Do you have a new suspect?

206
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:06,267
The paraffin test results
came in.

207
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,233
There's powder burn
on the victim's hand.

208
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,567
Most likely, it was suicide.

209
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:13,800
My condolences.

210
00:12:15,867 --> 00:12:22,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

211
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:40,600
[CAR HUMMING]

212
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:46,767
[DOOR OPENS]

213
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:55,633
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:13:13,367 --> 00:13:17,800
[CRYING, SOBBING]

215
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:24,733
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

216
00:13:39,933 --> 00:13:46,767
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

217
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:59,533
[TRAFFIC NOISES]

218
00:13:59,667 --> 00:14:04,267
[REPORTER] Mike Trinidad, known
 for being an investment guru

219
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,300
was found dead in his home
last night.

220
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:08,100
According to the authorities,

221
00:14:08,233 --> 00:14:10,933
he died because of suicide.

222
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:14,933
Last year, Trinidad built the
Yayaman Tayo Investment Fund

223
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:18,133
to help out poor people.

224
00:14:18,267 --> 00:14:21,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,200
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

226
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:23,633
[MILDRED] Love...

227
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,533
What now? What will happen
to our money?

228
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:33,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

229
00:14:45,933 --> 00:14:47,600
- Oh. Hey, man.
- Hey.

230
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:51,500
He was a nice guy.

231
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,400
I receive money
every end of the month

232
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,967
thanks to him.

233
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:57,733
It's been going on
for four months.

234
00:14:59,033 --> 00:15:01,500
He must be facing a big problem
for him to commit suicide.

235
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:03,500
I feel bad for him.

236
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,433
[CLEARS THROAT]
We won't be...

237
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:08,467
losing our money, right?

238
00:15:09,233 --> 00:15:10,967
I haven't received anything yet.

239
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:15,200
No, the money automatically
comes every end of the month.

240
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,300
You will receive it
on your account.

241
00:15:17,467 --> 00:15:18,600
That's good.

242
00:15:20,633 --> 00:15:22,633
His son is probably here, right?

243
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,667
I heard he's good.

244
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,767
He'll probably
take over everything.

245
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:32,433
I never thought he was
capable of doing this.

246
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,633
I'm used to hating him.

247
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,967
Because he was up there...

248
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:46,067
he was happy.

249
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:53,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

250
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:54,833
I don't know...

251
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:00,700
How could he do this?

252
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:05,700
Ma, that's enough.

253
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:11,067
You should go and rest.

254
00:16:11,933 --> 00:16:13,367
Take King with you.

255
00:16:14,867 --> 00:16:15,867
That's enough.

256
00:16:16,033 --> 00:16:23,333
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

257
00:16:23,433 --> 00:16:25,500
You should go.

258
00:16:26,133 --> 00:16:27,367
King.

259
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:46,233
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:50,233
[MUSIC BECOMES OMINOUS]

261
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,467
[SNAPS FINGERS]

262
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:07,400
I already assigned someone
to monitor Samuel Trinidad.

263
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:10,300
Let's have him abducted
